('https://www.phonearena.com/reviews/Motorola-Moto-X4-Review_id4461', '2017-12-18 15:00:00', '<img src="https://i-cdn.phonearena.com/images/review/4461-thumb/Motorola-Moto-X4-Review.jpg" alt="" hspace="5" vspace="2" align="left" /><br>The Moto X series isn\'t what it used to be. Since Lenovoâ€™s acquisition of Motorola\'s smartphone business, the once-high-end Moto X lineup has been demoted to a mid-range ranking, overtaken by the Z series as the Moto brand\'s top smartphone selection. But this year\'s Moto X4 has intrigued us nonetheless. In a nutshell, it is a mid-range handset with premium looks â€“ one that just barely eclipses the G seriesâ€™ spec sheet, but stands out with its fancy construction, dual-camera setup, and IP68 water resistance. It currently costs $350 unlocked on Motorola\'s website, $325 from Google with Android ...', 'Motorola Moto X4 Review', 'https://www.phonearena.com/reviews/Motorola-Moto-X4-Review_id4461', 'https://www.phonearena.com/feed/reviews'),
('https://www.phonearena.com/reviews/Nova-True-Wireless-Headphones-Review_id4446', '2017-11-17 14:01:00', '<img src="https://i-cdn.phonearena.com/images/review/4446-thumb/Nova-True-Wireless-Headphones-Review.jpg" alt="" hspace="5" vspace="2" align="left" /><div></div><div><br></div>If you\'re in the market for a pair of those fancy true wireless headphones, say like the Apple AirPods or Samsung Gear IconX', 'Nova True Wireless Headphones Review', 'https://www.phonearena.com/reviews/Nova-True-Wireless-Headphones-Review_id4446', 'https://www.phonearena.com/feed/reviews'),
('https://www.phonearena.com/reviews/OnePlus-5T-Review_id4454', '2017-11-27 14:13:00', '<img src="https://i-cdn.phonearena.com/images/review/4454-thumb/OnePlus-5T-Review.jpg" alt="" hspace="5" vspace="2" align="left" /><br>2017 can be argued as the year of the trends: from stretched-out 18:9 displays to dual-camera implementations to facial recognition security, all adopted by many of the flagships released this year. And you know what else they adopted? This crazy idea of ultra-premium pricing around the neighborhood of $1,000. <br><br>However, there\'s a new phone that adopts all of these newfound qualities, and then some, but without the $1,000 price tag. Enter the OnePlus 5T: the latest high-end smartphone from the Chinese company. At first glance, it could be perceived as a minuscule update, coming only a ...', 'OnePlus 5T Review', 'https://www.phonearena.com/reviews/OnePlus-5T-Review_id4454', 'https://www.phonearena.com/feed/reviews'),
